<BaseLayout 
  title="Research - Dr. Venkatapathy Subramanian"
  description="Research projects at the intersection of AI and Indian Knowledge Systems"
>
  <h1>Research</h1>
  
  <p class="lead">
    My research explores the intersection of Artificial Intelligence and Indian Knowledge Systems (IKS), 
    with a focus on developing culturally-grounded AI technologies that respect and extend traditional knowledge.
  </p>

  <section id="current-projects">
    <h2 class="section-title">Current Projects</h2>

    <div class="project">
      <h3>Agathiyam Tokenizer: Sandhi-Aware Tamil Tokenization</h3>
      <div class="card-tags">
        <span class="tag">NLP</span>
        <span class="tag">Tamil</span>
        <span class="tag">Tokenization</span>
        <span class="tag">Open Source</span>
      </div>
      <p>
        <strong>Overview:</strong> Traditional tokenization methods fail to capture the complex morphological 
        and phonological processes in Tamil, particularly sandhi (sound changes at morpheme boundaries). 
        Agathiyam is a tokenization system specifically designed for Tamil that understands these linguistic nuances.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Key Innovations:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Sandhi-aware segmentation that respects Tamil morphological rules</li>
        <li>Context-sensitive handling of compound words</li>
        <li>Integration with modern transformer architectures</li>
        <li>Improved performance on downstream Tamil NLP tasks by 12-18%</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>Collaborators:</strong> Anaadi AI Research Team<br>
        <strong>Status:</strong> Active Development | <a href="https://github.com/AnaadiAI" target="_blank">GitHub</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h3>Lilavati Reasoning SLM: Indian Mathematical Procedures in AI</h3>
      <div class="card-tags">
        <span class="tag">SLM</span>
        <span class="tag">Reasoning</span>
        <span class="tag">IKS</span>
        <span class="tag">Mathematics</span>
      </div>
      <p>
        <strong>Overview:</strong> This project develops small language models for mathematical reasoning 
        inspired by algorithmic procedures from Bhaskara II's 12th-century mathematical treatise, Lilavati. 
        The goal is to create interpretable, efficient models that embody traditional problem-solving approaches.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Key Features:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Symbolic arithmetic model architecture based on Lilavati's procedural methods</li>
        <li>Compact models (&lt;1B parameters) with strong reasoning capabilities</li>
        <li>Interpretable intermediate steps aligned with classical procedures</li>
        <li>Applications in educational contexts and low-resource settings</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>Impact:</strong> Demonstrates how historical mathematical traditions can inform modern AI architectures, 
        offering alternatives to purely data-driven approaches.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Status:</strong> Research Phase | Paper in preparation
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h3>Thirukkural Portal: AI-Enhanced Text Annotation</h3>
      <div class="card-tags">
        <span class="tag">Digital Humanities</span>
        <span class="tag">Tamil</span>
        <span class="tag">Multilingual</span>
        <span class="tag">Collaborative</span>
      </div>
      <p>
        <strong>Overview:</strong> A web-based platform for collaborative annotation and analysis of the Thirukkural, 
        one of the most celebrated works of Tamil literature. The platform uses AI to assist scholars in creating 
        and linking annotations across multiple translations and interpretations.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Features:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Multilingual interface supporting Tamil, English, Sanskrit, and other languages</li>
        <li>AI-powered suggestion system for related verses and commentaries</li>
        <li>Semantic search across translations and historical commentaries</li>
        <li>Collaborative annotation with version control</li>
        <li>Knowledge graph visualization of concepts and themes</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>Community:</strong> Used by 200+ scholars and students worldwide<br>
        <strong>Status:</strong> Active | <a href="#">Visit Portal</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h3>Kalanjiyam: Digital Repository for Indian Texts</h3>
      <div class="card-tags">
        <span class="tag">OCR</span>
        <span class="tag">Knowledge Graphs</span>
        <span class="tag">IKS</span>
        <span class="tag">Preservation</span>
      </div>
      <p>
        <strong>Overview:</strong> Kalanjiyam ("treasury" in Tamil) is an AI-powered digital repository designed 
        to preserve, digitize, and make searchable thousands of Indian classical texts across multiple languages 
        and scripts.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Technical Approach:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Custom OCR models trained on historical Indic scripts (Grantha, old Tamil, Devanagari)</li>
        <li>Multi-script recognition with 95%+ accuracy on printed texts</li>
        <li>Named entity recognition for persons, places, and concepts in classical texts</li>
        <li>Automated linking to external knowledge bases (Wikipedia, Wikidata)</li>
        <li>Cross-text semantic search and citation network analysis</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>Corpus:</strong> 5,000+ texts digitized, covering literature, medicine, astronomy, and philosophy<br>
        <strong>Status:</strong> Pilot Phase | Collaboration with universities and libraries
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h3>AI for Ayurveda: Clinical Decision Support</h3>
      <div class="card-tags">
        <span class="tag">Healthcare</span>
        <span class="tag">Ayurveda</span>
        <span class="tag">Clinical AI</span>
        <span class="tag">IKS</span>
      </div>
      <p>
        <strong>Overview:</strong> Developing AI systems to support Ayurvedic practitioners by extracting 
        knowledge from classical texts and clinical observations, creating decision support tools that 
        respect traditional diagnostic frameworks.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Components:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Knowledge extraction from Ayurvedic compendiums (Charaka Samhita, Sushruta Samhita)</li>
        <li>Prakriti (constitutional type) prediction models</li>
        <li>Herb-disease relationship mapping</li>
        <li>Integration with modern clinical data</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>Partners:</strong> Ayurvedic hospitals and research institutions<br>
        <strong>Status:</strong> Early Research | Ethics review in progress
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

